sql:
SELECT user_name
FROM users
WHERE user_id = (SELECT project_manager_id FROM projects WHERE project_id = 0);

external_knowledge:
- "creative minds" refers to engineers;
- "gears" metaphorically represent components;
- "heart of River City" refers to projects located in the "River City" area;
- "craftsmanship" is a metaphor for the effort or number of components one has modified;
- The SQL query focuses on counting the components modified by engineers in the specified location and retrieving the engineers' names and IDs.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT u.user_name
FROM users u
WHERE u.user_id IN (
  SELECT al.user_id
  FROM access_logs al
)
AND u.user_id NOT IN (
  SELECT DISTINCT av.changed_by
  FROM component_versions av
);

SELECT child.type_name AS component_type_name, parent.type_name AS parent_type_name
FROM component_types child
LEFT JOIN component_types parent ON child.parent_type_id = parent.component_type_id;
